# Project Conventions

- **Contract is law.** `@vm/shared` is the single source of truth for types,
  Zod schemas, routes, and the error model. Never redefine these in an app;
  import them. If the boundary must change, change `packages/shared` first.
- **Comments are precise and scarce.** Code should be self-explanatory. Only
  comment non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints. Never narrate code
  (no `// loop over users`).
- **TypeScript strict**, no `any`. Prefer small, single-responsibility modules.
- **Auth vs. authz are separate.** Authentication (identity from JWT) and
  authorization (role policy) are distinct, composable units — never one blob.
- **Validate at the edge, enforce in the domain.** Shape validation happens at
  the boundary (Zod); business invariants are enforced in the domain layer.
- **Commits are feature-based** and conventional (`feat(api): ...`,
  `feat(web): ...`, `chore:`, `build:`, `docs:`).
